Condition : 20 - Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved, details of: 
- CCTV; 
- General external lighting; 
- Security lighting; 
- Access control measures for residential core entrances; 
- Secured by Design accreditation measures and counter terrorism measures; on or around the buildings or within the site in the development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority 
and installed prior to the first occupation of the development. The details shall include the location and full specification of all lamps; light levels/spill; illumination, details of the lumieres to be used demonstrating that they will be 'warm white' wavelengths to minimise disturbance to protected species (bats); cameras (including view paths); and support structures. The details will also include an assessment of the impact of any such lighting on the surrounding residential environment. Prior to occupation of any of the units, details of a post installation inspection of external light levels, in particular the lux spill into the adjoining Richmond Park shall be submitted to and approved in writing to demonstrate that the built project meets the projected light level reductions and that impacts on protected species (bats) have been ameliorated. The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved and shall be maintained as such thereafter. 
Reason: To safeguard the security of the development and to ensure that any resulting general or security lighting and CCTV are appropriately located, designed to not adversely impact on neighbouring residential amenity or ecology, and are appropriate to the overall design of the development in accordance with policies 7.3, 7.4, 7.6 and 7.19 of the London Plan and Policy DMS1 and DMO4 of the Wandsworth Local Plan
